{
  "texts": [
    "However, the contrast of the FFDM images depends on the differences between breast tissues; those images can provide just structural information.",
    "One of the limitations of this type of mammographic image is that the highly dense breast tissues can mask the mass, as most of the fibro-glandular tissues have the same image gray levels of the lesions.",
    "This can lower the sensitivity in detecting tumors when breast density increases [8].",
    "Recently, Contrast Enhanced Spectral Mammography (CESM) was introduced in 2011 as a new image technique for mammogram screening.",
    "CESM provides improved visualization for mammographic images by combining low and high-energy breast images."
  ]
}